each edge from a raw dart tail to the next raw dart tail is a selected
`unboundedFrontierEdgeSet` edge, in one of the two ordered orientations.

This is the input-level handoff consumed by
`rawFaceSuccOrbit_nearby_edge_point_exterior_points_of_unboundedFrontierEdgeSet_edges`
and the raw edge-frontier source; it uses only the geometric face-successor
endpoint preservation and the actual frontier row on the raw dart edge. -/
theorem S2_agent_raw_orbit_edge_membership_source
